04:17.475 --> 04:19.608
Move it!

04:23.849 --> 04:25.882
Move!

04:31.222 --> 04:33.223
Out of the way!
Hey, man.

04:33.891 --> 04:36.226
Watch out.

04:44.268 --> 04:46.770
Drop it, or I'll shoot!

04:46.772 --> 04:48.104
Reagan!

05:01.319 --> 05:03.253
Reagan?

05:03.255 --> 05:06.089
Jamie?!

05:06.091 --> 05:07.624
Eddie!

05:07.626 --> 05:09.893
Get on your feet.

05:13.998 --> 05:15.966
Look what I got.

05:21.505 --> 05:23.273
Get off me!

05:25.010 --> 05:26.476
Let go!

05:37.054 --> 05:38.555
Her name was Amy Lin.

05:38.557 --> 05:40.123
She was just
15 years old.

05:40.125 --> 05:43.059
She's just a kid. Unbelievable.

05:43.061 --> 05:44.494
This all you guys got?

05:44.496 --> 05:46.262
No other security cameras?

05:46.264 --> 05:47.931
It's the only one
in the station.

05:47.933 --> 05:49.599
But you were working
the token booth, right?

05:49.601 --> 05:51.434
Yeah.
Well, did you see anything?

05:51.436 --> 05:53.737
You hear anything? A cry for help?
No, man.

05:53.739 --> 05:55.138
I was listening
to the Knick game, you know.

05:55.140 --> 05:57.073
I mean, listen. The motorman
blew the long and the short,

05:57.075 --> 05:59.242
and I knew something was up,
but by the time I ran out there,

05:59.244 --> 06:00.610
it was... it was too late.

06:00.612 --> 06:02.212
And you didn't see
the guy at all?

06:02.214 --> 06:05.215
No. Just-just his back as he was
running out of the exit.

06:05.217 --> 06:06.783
The end of the platform.

06:06.785 --> 06:07.984
Okay, did he have any

06:07.986 --> 06:09.586
outstanding
identifying features?

06:09.588 --> 06:12.255
A scar, a tattoo, any
clothes that stuck out?

06:12.257 --> 06:16.359
No, but... I think
I recognize the guy.

06:17.962 --> 06:19.229
So, you knew the guy?

06:19.231 --> 06:20.964
No, no, no, no.
I didn't know him, know him.

06:20.966 --> 06:23.033
He was just some guy who used
to hang out in the station.

06:23.035 --> 06:24.167
Used to?

06:24.169 --> 06:25.301
Yeah, look,
the guy got

06:25.303 --> 06:26.736
real mental problems,
so I figured

06:26.738 --> 06:28.805
maybe they sent him away,
or something happened to him,

06:28.807 --> 06:30.306
but I guess he's back.

06:30.308 --> 06:31.841
What kind of mental problems?
Look,

06:31.843 --> 06:35.078
I'm not a doctor, but the dude
had real problems in the head.

06:35.080 --> 06:37.414
You know, he would be
all mellow and calm, and then,

06:37.416 --> 06:38.915
all of a sudden, just snap,

06:38.917 --> 06:40.016
he'd flip out and go crazy.

06:40.018 --> 06:41.184
Crazy how?

06:41.186 --> 06:42.519
You know, he'd, like,
yell at people,

06:42.521 --> 06:44.020
get in their faces,
be abusive.

06:44.022 --> 06:45.221
You know, a real nut.

06:45.223 --> 06:46.356
Okay.

06:46.358 --> 06:47.557
Did this nut have a name?

06:47.559 --> 06:48.625
Not a real name,

06:48.627 --> 06:50.560
but people in the hood
called him the Hulk.

06:51.662 --> 06:52.829
The Hulk?

06:52.831 --> 06:54.197
Yeah, the Hulk.

06:55.533 --> 06:56.666
On account of

06:56.668 --> 06:57.934
when he got angry?

06:57.936 --> 06:59.602
Exactly.

06:59.604 --> 07:01.337
Great.

07:01.339 --> 07:03.339
Wonder if he turned green, too.

